This paper deals with existential rules and their use in databases and knowledge representation, which are topics closely related to logic and model theory. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science). The paper also discusses the use of these rules in databases, which suggests cs.DB (Databases) as another likely category. Additionally, the paper mentions the use of these rules in artificial intelligence, which suggests cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) as a possible category. The paper also discusses complexity bounds, which suggests cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) and cs.CC (Computational Complexity) as possible categories.
